examples: Leave those books alone! They are my property .
Important types of property include real property (land), personal property (other physical possessions), and intellectual property (rights over artistic creations, inventions, etc.).

definitions.definition: A piece of real estate , such as a parcel of land.
examples: There is a large house on the property .
He owns over ten properties in the country.

definitions.definition: Real estate ; the business of selling houses .
examples: He works in property as a housing consultant.

definitions.definition: The exclusive right of possessing , enjoying and disposing of a thing .
An attribute or abstract quality associated with an individual, object or concept.
examples: Charm is his most endearing property .

definitions.definition: An attribute or abstract quality which is characteristic of a class of objects.
examples: Matter can have many properties , including color, mass and density.

definitions.definition: An editable or read-only parameter associated with an application , component or class ; especially ( object-oriented programming ) one that encapsulates an underlying variable .
examples: You need to set the debugging property to "verbose".

definitions.definition: A prop , an object used in a dramatic production .
examples: Costumes and scenery are distinguished from property properly speaking.

definitions.definition: A script, book, screenplay , or the like that is on the market or has been bought for commercial production as a stage play, movie , or the like.

subdefinitions.definition: A produced stage play, movie , or the like.
